{"image_id": "CINF_2013_page_84", "image_size": [1275, 1650], "ocr": [{"text": "Cincinnati Financial Corporation - 2013 10-K - Page 82", "bbox": [435.0, 1566.8, 839.8, 1585.4]}, {"text": "$16 million lower during 2013, improving the 2013 loss ratio by approximately 6 percentage points compared with", "bbox": [104.2, 85.8, 1152.1, 109.1]}, {"text": "2012. Better pricing and risk selection also contributed to the improvement for both 2013 and 2012.", "bbox": [104.2, 110.8, 1015.5, 134.1]}, {"text": "We continue efforts to improve pricing precision through predictive analytics, which we believe will help to achieve", "bbox": [104.2, 160.8, 1155.9, 184.1]}, {"text": "long-term profitability. Rate increases in recent years, discussed in Personal Lines Insurance Premiums, should", "bbox": [104.2, 185.8, 1134.3, 209.1]}, {"text": "help lower loss ratios as the rate increases are earned. Those rate changes were implemented beginning in", "bbox": [104.2, 210.8, 1099.6, 234.1]}, {"text": "October of 2013, 2012, 2011, 2010 and 2009 and averaged approximately 10 percent, 9 percent, 8 percent,", "bbox": [104.2, 235.8, 1099.8, 259.1]}, {"text": "7 percent and 6 percent, respectively. In 2013, we began increasing our use of higher loss deductibles and actual", "bbox": [104.2, 260.8, 1151.8, 284.1]}, {"text": "cash value claims settlement for insured damage to older roofs. In addition, in 2013 we increased the number of", "bbox": [104.2, 285.8, 1139.4, 309.1]}, {"text": "property inspections conducted when homeowner policies renewed, and plan to further increase that number in", "bbox": [104.2, 310.8, 1133.6, 334.1]}, {"text": "2014. Inspections provide more opportunities for underwriting or pricing actions on a case-by-case basis. We also", "bbox": [104.2, 335.8, 1155.2, 359.1]}, {"text": "continue our gradual expansion into states less prone to catastrophe losses, which we believe will reduce variability", "bbox": [104.2, 360.8, 1171.7, 384.1]}, {"text": "in the long-term future catastrophe loss ratio. In recent years, we nonrenewed approximately 2,300 policies in", "bbox": [104.2, 385.8, 1116.2, 409.1]}, {"text": "Florida and Alabama that we believe were the most exposed to losses from hurricane damage, and we intend to", "bbox": [104.2, 410.8, 1140.6, 434.1]}, {"text": "nonrenew additional Florida policies in 2014 and 2015. Together these actions represent important steps we are", "bbox": [104.2, 435.8, 1139.1, 459.1]}, {"text": "taking to further improve homeowner results.", "bbox": [104.2, 460.8, 516.4, 484.1]}, {"text": "Other Personal", "bbox": [104.2, 510.8, 253.5, 534.1]}, {"text": "(Dollars in millions)", "bbox": [110.4, 557.0, 246.5, 575.5]}, {"text": "Years ended December 31,", "bbox": [648.6, 552.6, 874.3, 575.7]}, {"text": "2013-2012", "bbox": [944.4, 552.4, 1034.6, 575.5]}, {"text": "2012-2011", "bbox": [1065.6, 552.6, 1155.9, 575.7]}, {"text": "2013", "bbox": [627.1, 581.6, 668.8, 604.6]}, {"text": "2012", "bbox": [739.6, 581.8, 781.2, 604.9]}, {"text": "2011", "bbox": [852.4, 581.8, 894.1, 604.9]}, {"text": "Change %", "bbox": [942.4, 581.6, 1036.7, 604.6]}, {"text": "Change %", "bbox": [1067.3, 581.8, 1153.5, 604.9]}, {"text": "Written premiums", "bbox": [110.4, 611.0, 262.6, 634.0]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [602.1, 610.8, 612.5, 633.8]}, {"text": "117", "bbox": [647.9, 610.8, 679.2, 633.8]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [714.6, 611.0, 725.0, 634.0]}, {"text": "115", "bbox": [763.9, 611.0, 795.1, 634.0]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [827.1, 611.0, 837.5, 634.0]}, {"text": "104", "bbox": [876.4, 611.0, 907.6, 634.0]}, {"text": "2", "bbox": [1028.4, 610.8, 1038.9, 633.8]}, {"text": "11", "bbox": [1138.9, 611.0, 1159.7, 634.0]}, {"text": "Earned premiums", "bbox": [110.4, 640.1, 258.0, 663.2]}, {"text": "115", "bbox": [647.9, 639.9, 679.2, 663.0]}, {"text": "111", "bbox": [763.9, 640.1, 795.1, 663.2]}, {"text": "100", "bbox": [876.4, 640.1, 907.6, 663.2]}, {"text": "4", "bbox": [1028.4, 639.9, 1038.9, 663.0]}, {"text": "11", "bbox": [1138.9,